<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Lusting after someone you see on reality TV rarely leads to real-life romance, but that's what happened for West End star Georgina Castle. </p>

<p>The 28-year-old daughter of Wimbledon commentator Andrew Castle is courting Alex Marks, 33, after spotting him on Channel 5's The Bachelor, where 25 women compete for the affections of a handsome and eligible man. </p>

<p>'We have mutual friends, so we'd made contact previously, but during lockdown I got into The Bachelor,' Georgina tells me.</p>

<p>West End star Georgina Castle, 28, is courting Alex Marks, 33, after spotting him on Channel 5's The Bachelor (pictured together)</p>

<p>'It was meant to be light relief, but I had no clue I'd end up quite liking him. </p>

<p>'I reached out and we met for a socially distanced date and got drunk in Battersea Park.' </p>

<p>And now she's on holiday in Greece with Alex, a personal trainer from Kent. </p>

<p>Georgina, who starred in theatre hits Mamma Mia! and 9 To 5, admits that dating a fitness fanatic has its perks</p>

<p>Georgina, who starred in theatre hits Mamma Mia! and 9 To 5, admits that dating a fitness fanatic has its perks. </p>

<p>She gushes: 'We have been working out together and I'm finding a new passion for it.' </p>
